prompt: Tell me one type of insect. Answer concisely in one paragraph.
output: One type of insect is the butterfly, which belongs to the order Lepidoptera. Butterflies are known for their colorful wings and delicate bodies. They have four wings that are often brightly colored with patterns and designs. The life cycle of a butterfly includes four stages: egg, larva (caterpillar), pupa (chrysalis), and adult. Butterflies play an important role in pollination and are considered beneficial insects because they help plants reproduce. There are thousands of species of butterflies found all over the world, each with its own unique characteristics and behaviors. Some butterflies are migratory, while others stay in one area year-round. Overall, butterflies are fascinating creatures that add beauty and diversity to our natural environment.
